.TH LOWHUNT 1 "May 2026" "LowHunt v1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lowhunt \- fast public OSINT for authorized username and domain analysis
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lowhunt
[OPTIONS] <username> [username2 ...]
.br
.B lowhunt
\-d DOMAIN [OPTIONS]
.br
.B lowhunt
<username> \-d DOMAIN [OPTIONS]
.br
.B lowhunt
\-\-about
.br
.B lowhunt
\-\-explain TOPIC
.br
.B man
lowhunt
.SH DESCRIPTION
LowHunt is a native C reconnaissance tool for public-data-only OSINT on
authorized targets. It checks username footprints across platform manifests,
harvests passive hostnames for domains, supports combined investigation runs,
and summarizes findings with multiple execution engines and investigator-friendly
terminal output.
.PP
LowHunt does not bypass authentication or protections. Use it only on targets
you own or have explicit written permission to assess.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-u, \-\-username NAME
Add a username target.
.TP
.B \-d, \-\-domain DOMAIN
Run passive domain hostname harvesting.
.TP
.B \-b, \-\-source SOURCE
Select harvest source. Current values: crtsh, rapiddns, wayback, all.
.TP
.B \-l, \-\-limit N
Limit harvested hostnames.
.TP
.B \-\-preset NAME
Apply operator defaults: beginner, balanced, or aggressive.
.TP
.B \-f, \-\-fast
Trim the loaded platform set to the fast subset.
.TP
.B \-s, \-\-site NAME
Limit username scanning to one platform.
.TP
.B \-\-engine NAME
Choose execution engine: auto, threadpool, fusion, async, parallel, stabilizer, sync.
.TP
.B \-T, \-\-threads N
Set the requested concurrency budget. Above 50 threads, LowHunt checks local resources and warns before continuing on constrained systems.
.TP
.B \-t, \-\-timeout MS
Set the per-request timeout in milliseconds.
.TP
.B \-\-tor
Route requests through socks5://127.0.0.1:9050.
.TP
.B \-\-proxy URL
Use a custom proxy URL.
.TP
.B \-\-intel
Print the intelligence summary after the scan.
.TP
.B \-v
Enable verbose status output.
.TP
.B \-vv
Enable full verbose structured output, including not-found, unknown, and error rows.
.TP
.B \-o, \-\-output FILE
Write results to a file.
.TP
.B \-\-format FMT
Select output format: txt, json, csv.
.TP
.B \-\-nsfw
Include NSFW platforms.
.TP
.B \-\-list-sites
Print the loaded platform catalog.
.TP
.B \-\-list-sources
Print the wired passive harvest sources.
.TP
.B \-\-about
Print the banner and project metadata.
.TP
.B \-\-explain TOPIC
Explain a command or concept such as engine, fusion, harvest, or -vv.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print the current version.
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Show the help menu.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B lowhunt alice \-\-engine fusion \-vv
Fast structured scan of one username with high concurrency.
.TP
.B lowhunt \-u alice \-u bob \-\-threads 120 \-\-intel
Multi-target scan with explicit concurrency and post-run summary.
.TP
.B lowhunt \-d example.com \-b all \-o hosts.json \-\-format json
Harvest fused passive host intelligence and save it as JSON.
.TP
.B lowhunt alice bob \-d example.com \-b all \-\-intel
Run a combined investigation with profile scanning, passive harvest, and correlation.
.TP
.B lowhunt \-\-about
Show the project overview and repository details.
.TP
.B lowhunt \-\-explain engine
Explain engine selection and what each execution mode is good at.
.SH INSTALLATION
Managed local installers are provided under:
.IP
install/linux.sh
.br
install/macos.sh
.br
install/termux.sh
.br
install/windows.ps1
.br
install/windows.cmd
.PP
The installers place the application in a user-local directory, write a managed install manifest, create launchers, and add man page access for shell environments that support it.
.SH REPORTS
Each scan or harvest stores an offline report bundle under:
.IP
~/.lowhunt/output/reports/<target>/<timestamp>/
.PP
Bundles include CLI, TXT, and JSON artifacts. Combined investigations also
write a fused investigation summary with correlation confidence and narrative text.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR crt.sh (1)
